 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search College Ambassador IRL United States Remote Job details Job Type Contract Full Job Description Company Overview 
 IRL (http://www.irl.com/) is the leading group messaging social network that brings people together through events and shared experiences. With its wide range of in-app offerings, including personalized event suggestions using artificial intelligence, calendar integrations, messenger and private group pages, IRL deepens everyone's ability to connect through organic community-building and engaging social interaction. 
 Based on humans' natural group orientation and essential need to communicate, especially in the post-COVID era, IRL is building the future of interaction by translating these inherent needs onto one platform and encouraging users to do more together. 
 Responsibilities: 
 
We are looking for an outgoing, creative, and networking full-time student in their second, third year, or fourth year, either physically present on campus or remote, to be the connection between IRL and campus students. It is preferable if there is experience from project/event management, such as within the Student Union, Greek Life, or other where you have been taking ideas from scratch to success. Some of the Ambassador's tasks include helping us: 
 
Baseline compensation: $300-600 per month, depending on whether the Ambassador sticks to the core tasks or chooses to go above and beyond. 
Estimated time commitment: 5-8 hours/week :) 
 Onboard student organizations on IRL 
Increase student downloads (by posting on Facebook Groups, texting friends, blasting to mailing lists, etc) 
Find cool events going on in your school 
